<DocsLayout title="Backup & Import">
  <h1>Backup & Import</h1>
  <p class="text-lg text-slate-400">Export your configuration, restore it on another instance, or generate new pipelines from a JSON file.</p>

  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>Datanika supports exporting and importing your entire pipeline configuration as a single JSON file. This covers:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Connections</strong> &mdash; source and destination databases, APIs, files (32 types)</li>
    <li><strong>Uploads</strong> &mdash; dlt Extract + Load jobs</li>
    <li><strong>Pipelines</strong> &mdash; dbt orchestration (run, build, test, seed, snapshot)</li>
    <li><strong>Transformations</strong> &mdash; dbt SQL models with materialization, tests, and tags</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Export a Backup</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Go to <strong>Settings</strong> in the sidebar</li>
    <li>In the <strong>Backup & Restore</strong> section, click <strong>Export Backup</strong></li>
    <li>A <code>backup.json</code> file is downloaded with all your connections, uploads, pipelines, and transformations</li>
  </ol>
  <p>Sensitive credentials (passwords, API keys) are automatically replaced with <code>CHANGE_ME</code> in the export. You'll re-enter them after importing.</p>

  <h2>Restore from Backup</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Go to <strong>Settings</strong> &rarr; <strong>Backup & Restore</strong></li>
    <li>Click <strong>Restore from Backup</strong> and upload a JSON file</li>
    <li>If any items already exist with the same name, you'll be asked to resolve each conflict:
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Skip</strong> &mdash; keep your existing configuration, don't import</li>
        <li><strong>Overwrite</strong> &mdash; replace the existing item with the imported version</li>
        <li><strong>Rename</strong> &mdash; import as a copy (appends "Copy" to the name)</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>After import, update any <code>CHANGE_ME</code> passwords with real credentials</li>
  </ol>
  <p><strong>Import is non-destructive</strong> &mdash; it never deletes existing items. Only items in the JSON file are created or updated.</p>

  <h2>Use Cases</h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Scenario</th><th>How</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Migrate between environments</td><td>Export from staging, import into production</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Clone an organization's setup</td><td>Export, create new org, import</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Version-control your config</td><td>Export periodically, commit the JSON to git</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Generate pipelines with AI</td><td>Give the format spec to an AI assistant, import the result</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Bulk-create resources</td><td>Write the JSON by hand or with a script, import all at once</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>AI-Generated Configurations</h2>
  <p>You can use any AI assistant (ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, etc.) to generate Datanika configurations from a plain-English description:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Give the AI the <a href="https://github.com/datanika-io/datanika-core/blob/master/AI_IMPORT_GUIDE.md">Import Format Guide</a></li>
    <li>Describe what you want: <em>"I have a MySQL database with orders and customers. Load them into BigQuery, create staging models, and build a revenue summary."</em></li>
    <li>The AI generates a JSON file with connections, uploads, pipelines, and transformations</li>
    <li>Import the JSON via <strong>Settings &rarr; Restore from Backup</strong></li>
    <li>Enter your real passwords and run</li>
  </ol>
  <p>The AI never sees your real credentials &mdash; all sensitive fields are set to <code>CHANGE_ME</code>.</p>

  <h2>JSON Format</h2>
  <p>The import file is a JSON object with these top-level fields:</p>
  <pre><code>{
  "version": 2,
  "connections": [...],
  "uploads": [...],
  "pipelines": [...],
  "transformations": [...]
}</code></pre>
  <p>All sections are optional. Include only what you need.</p>
  <p>Full field reference: <a href="https://github.com/datanika-io/datanika-core/blob/master/AI_IMPORT_GUIDE.md">AI_IMPORT_GUIDE.md on GitHub</a></p>
</DocsLayout>
